OL,3,CHottest year on record: 2024 was first
OL,4,Cyear to break 1.5C warming threshold
OL,6,FThey say human-driven climate change
OL,7,Fwas the primary cause for these record
OL,8,Ftemperatures, while other factors such
OL,9,Fas the Pacific Ocean's "El Nino"
OL,10,Fweather phenomenon, which raises
OL,11,Fglobal temperatures also had an effect.
OL,13,FThe EU's Copernicus Climate Change
OL,14,FService (C3S) confirmed previous
OL,15,Fprojections that 2024 was the warmest
OL,16,Fon record globally and the first
OL,17,Fcalendar year that the average
OL,18,Ftemperature exceeded 1.5C above pre-
OL,19,Findustrial levels.
