OL,3,CHottest year on record: 2024 was first
OL,4,Cyear to break 1.5C warming threshold
OL,6,FMeanwhile Analysis from the Met
OL,7,FOffice, University of East Anglia and
OL,8,Fthe National Centre for Atmospheric
OL,9,FScience also found 2024 was the
OL,10,Fhottest on record, and "likely" the
OL,11,Ffirst year exceeding 1.5C.
OL,13,FClimate experts said a single year
OL,14,Fwith average temperatures of 1.5C
OL,15,Fabove pre-industrial levels did not
OL,16,Fmean the world had reached that level
OL,17,Fof global warming, though they issued
OL,18,Fwarnings about how close it now was.
