OL,3,CHottest year on record: 2024 was first
OL,4,Cyear to break 1.5C warming threshold
OL,6,FAccording to the Copernicus analysis,
OL,7,Ftemperatures were an estimated 1.6C
OL,8,Fabove the pre-industrial level of 1850-
OL,9,F1900, and 0.12C above 2023 ` which was
OL,10,Fthe previous hottest year on record.
OL,12,FIt was the warmest year on record for
OL,13,FEurope, with temperatures 1.47C above
OL,14,Fthe average for the 1991-2020
OL,15,Freference period, the figures show.
OL,17,FThe analysis also highlights that
OL,18,Fglobally, each of the past 10 years
OL,19,Fwere one of the warmest 10 years on
OL,20,Frecord.
