OL,4,Cyear to break 1.5C warming threshold
OL,6,FProfessor Rowan Sutton, director of
OL,7,Fthe Met Office Hadley Centre, said:
OL,8,F"By itself, 1.5C does not represent a
OL,9,Fcliff edge in terms of climate impacts.
OL,11,F"But every fraction of a degree rise
OL,12,Fin global temperature increases the
OL,13,Ffrequency and severity of extreme
OL,14,Fweather events, commits the world to
OL,15,Fgreater rises in sea level and
OL,16,Fincreases the risk of crossing
OL,17,Fpotential planet-altering tipping
OL,18,Fpoints such as breakdown of the Amazon
OL,19,Frainforest biome or ice sheet collapse
OL,20,Fin Greenland or the Antarctic.
